snippet.description:
"Me with words is like Beyonce' on a stage: Pure magic." So&nbsp;explains the expertise and passion of communications coach Amber Wright -- founder of Talk to Amber -- whose clients include well-known personalities, authors and corporations&nbsp;that want to learn how to effectively deliver&nbsp;their message in a way that connects with their audience. On this episode of the&nbsp;Support is Sexy&nbsp;podcast, Amber shares the important distinction between talking and presenting, how to have the&nbsp;right&nbsp;conversations and the power of practice.

 &nbsp;

 On this episode, we discuss:

  How to fill the gaps in the market. Top tips for giving a speech. The important distinction between talking and inventing. The meaning of "word laundry." How to have the&nbsp;right&nbsp;conversations as a woman entrepreneur. The three important types of communication. The power of practice and how many times you must do it to be a pro. Why 3 is the magic number.  &nbsp;

 Are you a woman entrepreneur who is ready to step into the spotlight and share your message with the world? You&nbsp;must&nbsp;consider podcast guesting! CLICK HERE to find out more! &nbsp;

